The paper presents a method for nonparametric system identification, which involves the estimation of Volterra series models. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including signal processing (cs.SI), machine learning (cs.LG), control systems (cs.SY), and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of regularization methods, which are commonly used in machine learning and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI, followed by cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SY, and cs.IT.
